sailpoint.object

Class RoleDetection

  • java.lang.Object
    • sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject
      • sailpoint.object.RoleDetection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject

    public class RoleDetection
extends AbstractXmlObject
    An object used to record information about which entitlements held by the identity were used in the detection of a role. This is calculated as a side effect of entitlement correlation, and not intended to be edited manually.
    See Also:

      • isMatch

        public boolean isMatch(RoleDetection other)
        Return true if one role detection is logically equal to another. First they must reference the same role, then they must have the same RoleTargets.

      • hasCompatibleTargets

        public boolean hasCompatibleTargets(java.util.List<RoleTarget> other)
        Return true if the RoleTargets in this detection are all included in another detection list. Used by EntitlementCorrelator when reconciling incremental detections. The list can include more targets than needed.

public void setItems(java.util.List<IdentityItem> items)
        Deprecated. use RoleDetection.setTargets(java.util.List)
